dct_title_s: Part of the Southern Hemisphere, shewing recent discoveries
dct_description_sm: Routes of Cooke in 1773 & 1774, Weddell in 1823, and Biscoe in 1831 & 1832 shown in blue, yellow, and red. Enderby Land, Graham Land, and Adelaide Island are shown. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 3, (1833), pp. 105-12; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.3 1833
dct_publisher_sm: London: published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by John Murray, Albemarle St., 1833.
